      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria, floating-point rounding effects, and solver-specific numerical diffusion must be quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error.",
      "rationale": "Solver error was not assessed. Iterative residuals were reported but no formal analysis of numerical diffusion or round-off effects was conducted. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented simulation protocol with independent peer review of setup files must be in place to prevent operator-induced errors in boundary conditions and material properties.",
      "rationale": "No formal use-error protocol exists. Boundary condition inputs were set by a single analyst without independent review. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The choice of turbulence closure and hemolysis damage model must be justified through sensitivity studies comparing at least two model forms against experimental data.",
      "rationale": "Only the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law damage model was used; no alternative model form was evaluated. Turbulence model sensitivity was not assessed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Probability distributions for all uncertain model inputs (viscosity, hematocrit, pump speed tolerance) must be characterized and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was initiated but input probability distributions for blood viscosity and hematocrit variability were assumed uniform without experimental characterization. Factor flagged as not-assessed at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample size must be sufficient to characterize inter-sample variability in hemolysis measurements; statistical power analysis must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Only three blood samples were used across all bench experiments; no statistical power analysis was performed. Sample size insufficient to characterize biological variability. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal parameter equivalency analysis must demonstrate that simulation input parameters match experimental conditions within quantified tolerances for all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "No parameter equivalency analysis was performed. Rotational speed and flow rate tolerances between CFD inputs and experimental set points were not formally compared. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
